Implementations like `ConcatenationDocumentJoiner` simply concatenate the document lists. The `join` method takes a map of queries to lists of document lists and returns a single list of documents.  For example:

```java
Map<Query, List<List<Document>>> documentsForQuery = ...;
DocumentJoiner documentJoiner = new ConcatenationDocumentJoiner();
List<Document> documents = documentJoiner.join(documentsForQuery);
